genresAdvancedInfo.name: japanese worship
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Japanese worship music is a genre of Christian music that is popular in Japan. The music is characterized by its simple melodies and heartfelt lyrics that express devotion and gratitude towards God. The songs are usually sung in Japanese and are accompanied by traditional instruments such as the shamisen, koto, and taiko drums. The genre has a strong following among Japanese Christians and has also gained popularity in other parts of the world.
